msgctxt "dn8:0.1"
msgid "Dīgha Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Long Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "dn8:0.2"
msgid "Mahāsīhanādasutta "
msgstr "The Longer Discourse on the Lion’s Roar "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts-cs1, pts-vp-pli1.161, sc1
msgctxt "dn8:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
#. VAR: uruññāyaṃ → ujuññāyaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn8:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā uruññāyaṃ viharati kaṇṇakatthale migadāye. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Ujuñña, in the deer park at Kaṇṇakatthala. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn8:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho acelo kassapo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then the naked ascetic Kassapa went up to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "dn8:1.4"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho acelo kassapo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he stood to one side, and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs2
msgctxt "dn8:2.1"
msgid "“sutaṃ metaṃ, bho gotama: "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, I have heard the following: "

# NOTE: See AN 10.94
msgctxt "dn8:2.2"
msgid "‘samaṇo gotamo sabbaṃ tapaṃ garahati, sabbaṃ tapassiṃ lūkhājīviṃ ekaṃsena upakkosati upavadatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama criticizes all forms of mortification. He categorically condemns and denounces those self-mortifiers who live rough.’ "

msgctxt "dn8:2.3"
msgid "Ye te, bho gotama, evamāhaṃsu: ‘samaṇo gotamo sabbaṃ tapaṃ garahati, sabbaṃ tapassiṃ lūkhājīviṃ ekaṃsena upakkosati upavadatī’ti, kacci te bhoto gotamassa vuttavādino, na ca bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkhanti, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākaronti, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānuvādo gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgacchati? "
msgstr "Do those who say this repeat what the Buddha has said, and not misrepresent him with an untruth? Is their explanation in line with the teaching? Are there any legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism? "

msgctxt "dn8:2.4"
msgid "Anabbhakkhātukāmā hi mayaṃ bhavantaṃ gotaman”ti. "
msgstr "For we don’t want to misrepresent Master Gotama.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs3, pts-vp-pli1.162, sc2
msgctxt "dn8:3.1"
msgid "“Ye te, kassapa, evamāhaṃsu: ‘samaṇo gotamo sabbaṃ tapaṃ garahati, sabbaṃ tapassiṃ lūkhājīviṃ ekaṃsena upakkosati upavadatī’ti, na me te vuttavādino, abbhācikkhanti ca pana maṃ te asatā abhūtena. "
msgstr "“Kassapa, those who say this do not repeat what I have said. They misrepresent me with what is false, baseless, and untrue. "

msgctxt "dn8:3.2"
msgid "Idhāhaṃ, kassapa, ekaccaṃ tapassiṃ lūkhājīviṃ passāmi dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannaṃ. "
msgstr "With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I see some self-mortifier who lives rough reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. "

msgctxt "dn8:3.3"
msgid "Idha panāhaṃ, kassapa, ekaccaṃ tapassiṃ lūkhājīviṃ passāmi dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannaṃ. "
msgstr "But I see another self-mortifier who lives rough reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "dn8:3.4"
msgid "Idhāhaṃ, kassapa, ekaccaṃ tapassiṃ appadukkhavihāriṃ passāmi dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannaṃ. "
msgstr "I see some self-mortifier who takes it easy reborn in a place of loss. "

msgctxt "dn8:3.5"
msgid "Idha panāhaṃ, kassapa, ekaccaṃ tapassiṃ appadukkhavihāriṃ passāmi dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannaṃ. "
msgstr "But I see another self-mortifier who takes it easy reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm. "

msgctxt "dn8:3.6"
msgid "Yohaṃ, kassapa, imesaṃ tapassīnaṃ evaṃ āgatiñca gatiñca cutiñca upapattiñca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāmi, sohaṃ kiṃ sabbaṃ tapaṃ garahissāmi, sabbaṃ vā tapassiṃ lūkhājīviṃ ekaṃsena upakkosissāmi upavadissāmi? "
msgstr "Since I truly understand the coming and going, passing away and rebirth of these self-mortifiers in this way, how could I criticize all forms of mortification, or categorically condemn and denounce those self-mortifiers who live rough? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs4, sc4
msgctxt "dn8:4.1"
msgid "Santi, kassapa, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā paṇḍitā nipuṇā kataparappavādā vālavedhirūpā. Te bhindantā maññe caranti paññāgatena diṭṭhigatāni. "
msgstr "There are some clever ascetics and brahmins who are subtle, accomplished in the doctrines of others, hair-splitters. You’d think they live to demolish convictions with their intellect. "

msgctxt "dn8:4.2"
msgid "Tehipi me saddhiṃ ekaccesu ṭhānesu sameti, ekaccesu ṭhānesu na sameti. "
msgstr "They agree with me in some matters and disagree in others. "

msgctxt "dn8:4.3"
msgid "Yaṃ te ekaccaṃ vadanti ‘sādhū’ti, mayampi taṃ ekaccaṃ vadema ‘sādhū’ti. "
msgstr "Some of the things that they applaud, I also applaud. "

msgctxt "dn8:4.4"
msgid "Yaṃ te ekaccaṃ vadanti ‘na sādhū’ti, mayampi taṃ ekaccaṃ vadema ‘na sādhū’ti. "
msgstr "Some of the things that they don’t applaud, I also don’t applaud. "

msgctxt "dn8:4.5"
msgid "Yaṃ te ekaccaṃ vadanti ‘sādhū’ti, mayaṃ taṃ ekaccaṃ vadema ‘na sādhū’ti. "
msgstr "But some of the things that they applaud, I don’t applaud. "

msgctxt "dn8:4.6"
msgid "Yaṃ te ekaccaṃ vadanti ‘na sādhū’ti, mayaṃ taṃ ekaccaṃ vadema ‘sādhū’ti. "
msgstr "And some of the things that they don’t applaud, I do applaud. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.163, sc5
msgctxt "dn8:4.7"
msgid "Yaṃ mayaṃ ekaccaṃ vadema ‘sādhū’ti, parepi taṃ ekaccaṃ vadanti ‘sādhū’ti. "
msgstr "Some of the things that I applaud, others also applaud. "

msgctxt "dn8:4.8"
msgid "Yaṃ mayaṃ ekaccaṃ vadema ‘na sādhū’ti, parepi taṃ ekaccaṃ vadanti ‘na sādhū’ti. "
msgstr "Some of the things that I don’t applaud, they also don’t applaud. "

msgctxt "dn8:4.9"
msgid "Yaṃ mayaṃ ekaccaṃ vadema ‘na sādhū’ti, pare taṃ ekaccaṃ vadanti ‘sādhū’ti. "
msgstr "But some of the things that I don’t applaud, others do applaud. "

msgctxt "dn8:4.10"
msgid "Yaṃ mayaṃ ekaccaṃ vadema ‘sādhū’ti, pare taṃ ekaccaṃ vadanti ‘na sādhū’ti. "
msgstr "And some of the things that I do applaud, others don’t applaud. "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn8:4.11"
msgid "1. Samanuyuñjāpanakathā "
msgstr "1. Examination "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs5, sc6
msgctxt "dn8:5.1"
msgid "Tyāhaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadāmi: "
msgstr "I go up to them and say: "

msgctxt "dn8:5.2"
msgid "‘yesu no, āvuso, ṭhānesu na sameti, tiṭṭhantu tāni ṭhānāni. "
msgstr "‘Let us leave aside those matters on which we disagree. "

msgctxt "dn8:5.3"
msgid "Yesu ṭhānesu sameti, tattha viññū samanuyuñjantaṃ samanugāhantaṃ samanubhāsantaṃ satthārā vā satthāraṃ saṅghena vā saṅghaṃ: "
msgstr "But there are some matters on which we agree. Regarding these, sensible people, pursuing, pressing, and grilling, would compare teacher with teacher or community with community: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn8:5.4"
msgid "“ye imesaṃ bhavataṃ dhammā akusalā akusalasaṅkhātā, sāvajjā sāvajjasaṅkhātā, asevitabbā asevitabbasaṅkhātā, na alamariyā na alamariyasaṅkhātā, kaṇhā kaṇhasaṅkhātā. "
msgstr "“There are things that are unskillful, blameworthy, not to be cultivated, unworthy of the noble ones, and dark—and are reckoned as such. "

msgctxt "dn8:5.5"
msgid "Ko ime dhamme anavasesaṃ pahāya vattati, samaṇo vā gotamo, pare vā pana bhonto gaṇācariyā”ti? "
msgstr "Who behaves like they’ve totally given these things up: the ascetic Gotama, or the teachers of other communities?”’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs6, sc7
msgctxt "dn8:6.1"
msgid "Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, kassapa, vijjati, yaṃ viññū samanuyuñjantā samanugāhantā samanubhāsantā evaṃ vadeyyuṃ: "
msgstr "It’s possible that they might say: "

msgctxt "dn8:6.2"
msgid "‘ye imesaṃ bhavataṃ dhammā akusalā akusalasaṅkhātā, sāvajjā sāvajjasaṅkhātā, asevitabbā asevitabbasaṅkhātā, na alamariyā na alamariyasaṅkhātā, kaṇhā kaṇhasaṅkhātā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn8:6.3"
msgid "Samaṇo gotamo ime dhamme anavasesaṃ pahāya vattati, yaṃ vā pana bhonto pare gaṇācariyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama behaves like he’s totally given those unskillful things up, compared with the teachers of other communities.’ "

msgctxt "dn8:6.4"
msgid "Itiha, kassapa, viññū samanuyuñjantā samanugāhantā samanubhāsantā amheva tattha yebhuyyena pasaṃseyyuṃ. "
msgstr "And that’s how, when sensible people pursue the matter, they will mostly praise us. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-cs7, sc8
msgctxt "dn8:7.1"
msgid "Aparampi no, kassapa, viññū samanuyuñjantaṃ samanugāhantaṃ samanubhāsantaṃ satthārā vā satthāraṃ saṅghena vā saṅghaṃ: "
msgstr "In addition, sensible people, engaging, pressing, and grilling, would compare teacher with teacher or community with community: "

msgctxt "dn8:7.2"
msgid "‘ye imesaṃ bhavataṃ dhammā kusalā kusalasaṅkhātā, anavajjā anavajjasaṅkhātā, sevitabbā sevitabbasaṅkhātā, alamariyā alamariyasaṅkhātā, sukkā sukkasaṅkhātā. "
msgstr "‘There are things that are skillful, blameless, worth cultivating, worthy of the noble ones, and bright—and are reckoned as such. "

msgctxt "dn8:7.3"
msgid "Ko ime dhamme anavasesaṃ samādāya vattati, samaṇo vā gotamo, pare vā pana bhonto gaṇācariyā’ti? "
msgstr "Who proceeds having totally undertaken these things: the ascetic Gotama, or the teachers of other communities?’ "

