#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn8:12.5"
msgid "2. Ariyaaṭṭhaṅgikamagga "
msgstr "2. The Noble Eightfold Path "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs13, sc14
#. VAR: dakkhati → dakkhiti (bj) | dākkhīti (pts1)
msgctxt "dn8:13.1"
msgid "Atthi, kassapa, maggo atthi paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipanno sāmaññeva ñassati sāmaṃ dakkhati: "
msgstr "There is, Kassapa, a path, there is a practice, practicing in accordance with which you will know and see for yourself: "

# NOTE: Note the va, which is ignored by RD and MW. Comm, however, takes it in exclusive sense, referring back to the Brahmajala. The usage is similar to, eg. eso’va maggo, natthi anno, and, given the context, it seems likely this exclusive sense was meant here.
msgctxt "dn8:13.2"
msgid "‘samaṇova gotamo kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Only the ascetic Gotama’s words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training.’ "

msgctxt "dn8:13.3"
msgid "Katamo ca, kassapa, maggo, katamā ca paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipanno sāmaññeva ñassati sāmaṃ dakkhati: "
msgstr "And what is that path? "

msgctxt "dn8:13.4"
msgid "‘samaṇova gotamo kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn8:13.5"
msgid "Ayameva ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo. "
msgstr "It is simply this noble eightfold path, that is: "

msgctxt "dn8:13.6"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—sammādiṭṭhi sammāsaṅkappo sammāvācā sammākammanto sammāājīvo sammāvāyāmo sammāsati sammāsamādhi. "
msgstr "right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. "

msgctxt "dn8:13.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, kassapa, maggo, ayaṃ paṭipadā, yathāpaṭipanno sāmaññeva ñassati sāmaṃ dakkhati ‘samaṇova gotamo kālavādī bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī’”ti. "
msgstr "This is the path, this is the practice, practicing in accordance with which you will know and see for yourself: ‘Only the ascetic Gotama’s words are timely, true, and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training.’” "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn8:13.8"
msgid "3. Tapopakkamakathā "
msgstr "3. Practicing Self-Mortification "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs14, pts-vp-pli1.166, sc15
msgctxt "dn8:14.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, acelo kassapo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, Kassapa said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "dn8:14.2"
msgid "“imepi kho, āvuso gotama, tapopakkamā etesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ sāmaññasaṅkhātā ca brahmaññasaṅkhātā ca. "
msgstr "“Reverend Gotama, those ascetics and brahmins consider these practices of self-mortification to be what makes someone a true ascetic or brahmin. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.3"
msgid "Acelako hoti, muttācāro, hatthāpalekhano, naehibhaddantiko, natiṭṭhabhaddantiko, nābhihaṭaṃ, na uddissakataṃ, na nimantanaṃ sādiyati. "
msgstr "They go naked, ignoring conventions. They lick their hands, and don’t come or wait when asked. They don’t consent to food brought to them, or food prepared on purpose for them, or an invitation for a meal. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.4"
msgid "So na kumbhimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti, na kaḷopimukhā paṭiggaṇhāti, na eḷakamantaraṃ, na daṇḍamantaraṃ, na musalamantaraṃ, na dvinnaṃ bhuñjamānānaṃ, na gabbhiniyā, na pāyamānāya, na purisantaragatāya, na saṅkittīsu, na yattha sā upaṭṭhito hoti, na yattha makkhikā saṇḍasaṇḍacārinī, na macchaṃ, na maṃsaṃ, na suraṃ, na merayaṃ, na thusodakaṃ pivati. "
msgstr "They don’t receive anything from a pot or bowl; or from someone who keeps sheep, or who has a weapon or a shovel in their home; or where a couple is eating; or where there is a woman who is pregnant, breastfeeding, or who has a man in her home; or where there’s a dog waiting or flies buzzing. They accept no fish or meat or liquor or wine, and drink no beer. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.5"
msgid "So ekāgāriko vā hoti ekālopiko, dvāgāriko vā hoti dvālopiko … sattāgāriko vā hoti sattālopiko; "
msgstr "They go to just one house for alms, taking just one mouthful, or two houses and two mouthfuls, up to seven houses and seven mouthfuls. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.6"
msgid "ekissāpi dattiyā yāpeti, dvīhipi dattīhi yāpeti … sattahipi dattīhi yāpeti; "
msgstr "They feed on one saucer a day, two saucers a day, up to seven saucers a day. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.7"
msgid "ekāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti, dvīhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti … sattāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāreti. Iti evarūpaṃ addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharati. "
msgstr "They eat once a day, once every second day, up to once a week, and so on, even up to once a fortnight. They live committed to the practice of eating food at set intervals. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "dn8:14.8"
msgid "Imepi kho, āvuso gotama, tapopakkamā etesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ sāmaññasaṅkhātā ca brahmaññasaṅkhātā ca. "
msgstr "Those ascetics and brahmins also consider these practices of self-mortification to be what makes someone a true ascetic or brahmin. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.9"
msgid "Sākabhakkho vā hoti, sāmākabhakkho vā hoti, nīvārabhakkho vā hoti, daddulabhakkho vā hoti, haṭabhakkho vā hoti, kaṇabhakkho vā hoti, ācāmabhakkho vā hoti, piññākabhakkho vā hoti, tiṇabhakkho vā hoti, gomayabhakkho vā hoti, vanamūlaphalāhāro yāpeti pavattaphalabhojī. "
msgstr "They eat herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. They survive on forest roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.167, sc17
msgctxt "dn8:14.10"
msgid "Imepi kho, āvuso gotama, tapopakkamā etesaṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ sāmaññasaṅkhātā ca brahmaññasaṅkhātā ca. "
msgstr "Those ascetics and brahmins also consider these practices of mortification to be what makes someone a true ascetic or brahmin. "

# NOTE: vekaṭikopi hoti vikaṭabhojanānuyogamanuyutto means eating urine, etc. see MN 12.
msgctxt "dn8:14.11"
msgid "Sāṇānipi dhāreti, masāṇānipi dhāreti, chavadussānipi dhāreti, paṃsukūlānipi dhāreti, tirīṭānipi dhāreti, ajinampi dhāreti, ajinakkhipampi dhāreti, kusacīrampi dhāreti, vākacīrampi dhāreti, phalakacīrampi dhāreti, kesakambalampi dhāreti, vāḷakambalampi dhāreti, ulūkapakkhikampi dhāreti, "
msgstr "They wear robes of sunn hemp, mixed hemp, corpse-wrapping cloth, rags, lodh tree bark, antelope hide (whole or in strips), kusa grass, bark, wood-chips, human hair, horse-tail hair, or owls’ wings. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.12"
msgid "kesamassulocakopi hoti kesamassulocanānuyogamanuyutto, "
msgstr "They tear out hair and beard, committed to this practice. "

#. VAR: ubbhaṭṭhakopi → ubbhaṭṭhikopi (mr)
msgctxt "dn8:14.13"
msgid "ubbhaṭṭhakopi hoti āsanapaṭikkhitto, "
msgstr "They constantly stand, refusing seats. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.14"
msgid "ukkuṭikopi hoti ukkuṭikappadhānamanuyutto, "
msgstr "They squat, committed to persisting in the squatting position. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.15"
msgid "kaṇṭakāpassayikopi hoti kaṇṭakāpassaye seyyaṃ kappeti, "
msgstr "They lie on a mat of thorns, making a mat of thorns their bed. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.16"
msgid "phalakaseyyampi kappeti, thaṇḍilaseyyampi kappeti, "
msgstr "They make their bed on a plank, or the bare ground. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.17"
msgid "ekapassayikopi hoti "
msgstr "They lie only on one side. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.18"
msgid "rajojalladharo, "
msgstr "They wear dust and dirt. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.19"
msgid "abbhokāsikopi hoti "
msgstr "They stay in the open air. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.20"
msgid "yathāsanthatiko, "
msgstr "They sleep wherever they lay their mat. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.21"
msgid "vekaṭikopi hoti vikaṭabhojanānuyogamanuyutto, "
msgstr "They eat unnatural things, committed to the practice of eating unnatural foods. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.22"
msgid "apānakopi hoti apānakattamanuyutto, "
msgstr "They don’t drink, committed to the practice of not drinking liquids. "

msgctxt "dn8:14.23"
msgid "sāyatatiyakampi udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharatī”ti. "
msgstr "They’re committed to the practice of immersion in water three times a day, including the evening.” "

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn8:14.24"
msgid "4. Tapopakkamaniratthakathā "
msgstr "4. The Uselessness of Self-Mortification "

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: pts-cs15, sc18
msgctxt "dn8:15.1"
msgid "“Acelako cepi, kassapa, hoti, muttācāro, hatthāpalekhano … pe … iti evarūpaṃ addhamāsikampi pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharati. "
msgstr "“Kassapa, someone may practice all those forms of self-mortification, "

msgctxt "dn8:15.2"
msgid "Tassa cāyaṃ sīlasampadā cittasampadā paññāsampadā abhāvitā hoti asacchikatā. Atha kho so ārakāva sāmaññā ārakāva brahmaññā. "
msgstr "but if they haven’t developed and realized any accomplishment in ethics, mind, and wisdom, they are far from being a true ascetic or brahmin. "

msgctxt "dn8:15.3"
msgid "Yato kho, kassapa, bhikkhu averaṃ abyāpajjaṃ mettacittaṃ bhāveti, āsavānañca khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "But take a mendicant who develops a heart of love, free of enmity and ill will. And they realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. "

msgctxt "dn8:15.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, kassapa, bhikkhu samaṇo itipi brāhmaṇo itipi. "
msgstr "When they achieve this, they’re called a mendicant who is a ‘true ascetic’ and also ‘a true brahmin’. "

